Week 6: VPNs
Theory:
Types: Site-to-Site, Remote Access VPN
IPSec vs SSL VPN
Authentication methods (PSK, certificates)

Lab:


Configure site-to-site VPN between two Cisco routers
crypto isakmp policy 10
 encryption aes
 hash sha
 authentication pre-share
 group 2
crypto isakmp key MySecretKey address 192.168.2.1
crypto ipsec transform-set MySET esp-aes esp-sha-hmac
crypto map VPN 10 ipsec-isakmp
 set peer 192.168.2.1
 set transform-set MySET
 match address 101
interface g0/0
 crypto map VPN




Week 7: IDS/IPS & Threat Detection
Theory:
IDS vs IPS
Signatures and anomaly detection
Common attacks (DoS, MITM, brute force)

Lab:

Configure basic Snort IDS on Linux
sudo apt install snort -y
sudo snort -A console -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -i eth0




Week 8: Security Monitoring Tools
Theory:
SolarWinds, Netcool, Nagios, PRTG basics
Event logs, SNMP, Syslog
Lab:

Install Nagios Core and monitor a host
sudo apt install nagios4 nagios-plugins -y
sudo systemctl start nagios4
sudo systemctl enable nagios4
# Access web UI at http://<server-ip>/nagios4

