Phase 3: Cloud Security Fundamentals (Weeks 9–12)
Goal: Understand AWS basics, VPCs, IAM, and hybrid cloud security.

Week 9: AWS Networking Basics
Theory:
VPC, Subnets, Internet Gateway, NAT Gateway
Security Groups vs NACLs
Lab:


Create a VPC with 2 subnets
# AWS CLI example
aws ec2 create-vpc --cidr-block 10.0.0.0/16
aws ec2 create-subnet --vpc-id <vpc-id> --cidr-block 10.0.1.0/24
aws ec2 create-subnet --vpc-id <vpc-id> --cidr-block 10.0.2.0/24


Week 10: IAM & Security Policies
Theory:
IAM users, groups, roles, and policies
Principle of Least Privilege


Lab:
Create an IAM user with S3 read-only access
aws iam create-user --user-name AuditUser
aws iam attach-user-policy --user-name AuditUser --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess

Week 11: Cloud Firewall & VPN
Theory:
Security Groups vs NACLs
Site-to-Site VPN to AWS




Lab:
Configure security group for web server access
aws ec2 create-security-group --group-name WebSG --description "Web Server SG" --vpc-id <vpc-id>
aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress --group-id <sg-id> --protocol tcp --port 80 --cidr 0.0.0.0/0




Week 12: Cloud Monitoring & Logging
Theory:
CloudWatch, CloudTrail
Logging, alerts, and incident response




Lab:
Enable CloudTrail and view events
aws cloudtrail create-trail --name MyTrail --s3-bucket-name my-cloudtrail-logs
aws cloudtrail start-logging --name MyTrail

